{
  "stem": "12462.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The defendant, Hjalmar Schacht, who had been the Reich Minister of Economics, and who'd been very active during the first years of the Nazi regime in the rearmament of Germany, but then had had a fuss with Hermann Goering and had resigned as Reich minister.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And although we indicted him for his earlier activities, the tribunal found him not guilty.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the third one was Hans Fritzsche, one of my two defendants, who was found not guilty on the notion that he had not incited, intentionally, the Nazi regime to kill its opponents, and particularly the Jews.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first case against the medical officers, officials, who had committed experiments on concentration camp inmates and on prisoners-- and Polish women who were not even in concentration camp had their legs cut open and all that so that they could experiment with sulfanilamide, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Go ahead.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think that would have been December, 1946, or very early in '47, because we were very close to being ready by the end of the first trial to go into that case, as well as the Milch case, the second case.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we had-- [CLEARS THROAT] had to wait a while to-- to-- to get the translators adjusted and to get new defense counsel-- had to be appointed and have a chance to meet their defense, and so on.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were-- the 12 subsequent trials were all held in the courthouse.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But-- and at one time, there was as many as four trials going on at once.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The IG Farben case, in which I was chief of the IG Farben trial team, was held in the main court room, because that-- we had 24 defendants.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was the only room which-- where you could really get that many defendants in.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
